<TITLE> School student killed as bus runs over 3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 25 (bdnews24.com)A six-year old school girl was killed when a bus ran over three school students on Thursday near Kashem Jute Mills in Sitakunds on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway, police said. Robiul Hasan Rafee, a class one student of MA Kashem Raja School, was crossing the highway along with two of her classmates after school at around 11am. A Mirersarai-bound bus of Choice Paribahan coming from Chittagong ran over them, Ameer Faruque, highway police sergeant, told bdnews24.com. Rafee died on the spot while the other two, were injured. Sonia Akter, 5, sustained serious injuries and was later admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. The third child received first aid. Sgt Faruque added that immediately after the accident, the students of the school and the locals chased and stopped the bus and torched it. They also barricaded the highway. Police intervened at around 11:30 am and cleared the traffic gridlock. Rafee's body has been sent to CMCH for autopsy, police said. bdne
